r-radius: 50%;\n    display: inline-flex;\n    align-items: center;\n    justify-content: center;\n    flex-shrink: 0;\n  }\n  .time {\n    font-weight: 600;\n    font-variant-numeric: tabular-nums;\n    color: #b91c1c;\n    min-width: 3.5rem;\n  }\n  .root-cause {\n    background: #fff;\n    border: 1px solid #ddd;\n    border-radius: 4px;\n    padding: 1rem 1.25rem;\n  }\n  ul.actions {\n    padding-left: 1.25rem;\n  }\n  ul.actions li {\n    margin-bottom: 0.5rem;\n  }\n  footer {\n    margin-top: 2.5rem;\n    font-size: 0.8rem;\n    color: #777;\n    border-top: 1px solid #ddd;\n    padding-top: 0.75rem;\n  }\n</style>\n</head>\n<body>\n\n<h1>Incident Report</h1>\n\n<h2>Summary</h2>\n<p class=\"summary\">\n  Checkout API returned 500s for 12 minutes due to a database connection pool exhaustion.\n</p>\n\n<h2>Timeline</h2>\n<ol class=\"timeline\">\n  <li><span class=\"time\">14:02</span> <span>Deploy shipped to production.</span></li>\n  <li><span class=\"time\">14:10</span> <span>Traffic spike began, increasing load on the checkout service.</span></li>\n  <li><span class=\"time\">14:12</span> <span>Alerts fired for elevated 500 error rate on the Checkout API.</span></li>\n  <li><span class=\"time\">14:14</span> <span>Database connection pool size reverted to previous configuration.</span></li>\n  <li><span class=\"time\">14:14</span> <span>Service recovered; error rate returned to normal.</span></li>\n</ol>\n\n<h2>Root Cause</h2>\n<div class=\"root-cause\">\n  <p>\n    The 14:02 deploy reduced the database connection pool size for the Checkout API.\n    When traffic spiked at 14:10, the smaller pool was unable to serve the increased\n    volume of concurrent requests, causing connections to be exhausted. Requests\n    that could not acquire a database connection failed with HTTP 500 errors until\n    the pool size was reverted at 14:14, after which the service immediately recovered.\n  </p>\n</div>\n\n<h2>Action Items</h2>\n<ul class=\"actions\">\n  <li>Add automated load testing to the deploy pipeline to catch connection pool\n    sizing regressions before they reach production.</li>\n  <li>Add monitoring and alerting on database connection pool utilization so\n    exhaustion is detected before it causes customer-facing errors.</li>\n</ul>\n\n<footer>\n  Generated incident postmortem &mdash; internal record.\n</footer>\n\n</body>\n</html>\n","structuredPatch":[],"originalFile":null,"userModified":false},"sourceToolAssistantUUID":"19d98ff5-20f1-4088-a46a-bf565db8c168","userType":"external","entrypoint":"sdk-cli","cwd":"/Users/boeschj/Documents/GitHub/parchment/bench/.runs/2026-07-12T15-07-38-053Z/incident-report/html/rep-1","sessionId":"37bd3041-bd3d-4bda-8287-dede2c437731","version":"2.1.207","gitBranch":"main"}
